						               													<description>&amp;quot;Stargard Solstice: Operation Solstice and the Soviet Pomeranian Campaign 1945&amp;quot; is a wargame recreating the campaigns in Pomerania from 15th February - 6th March, 1945.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game starts with one of the last German offensives of 1945, &amp;lsquo;Operation Solstice&amp;rsquo;. At the beginning German General Guderian had planned a pincer move to relieve K&amp;uuml;strin, but Hitler wanted to save troops to retake Budapest. This resulted in changing objectives to the relief of Festung Arnswalde and trying to cut the Soviet supply route towards K&amp;uuml;strin. The historical objective for the Soviets was to drive the Germans out of Pomerania and thereby protect their right flank while preparing to take K&amp;uuml;strin and make the final thrust towards Berlin.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Stargard Solstice&amp;trade; is taught in 30 minutes and easy to digest yet a challenge even for the more experienced players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is built around the same system of wargaming rules that shaped Plan West, K&amp;#195;&amp;#182;nigsberg '45 and Army Group Narwa and utilizes a Command chit-pull system to activate HQ, which in turn allow their controlled combat units to move and attack.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game Scale:&amp;#10;Game Turn: 2 days&amp;#10;Hex: about 3 to about 4 km&amp;#10;Units: Battalion to Division&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game Inventory:&amp;#10;One 23.5 x 33&amp;quot; (A1) full color map&amp;#10;Two dual-side printed countersheet (286 9/16&amp;quot; (15mm) counters)&amp;#10;One 16-page rulebook&amp;#10;Two single-side printed Player Aid Cards&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Solitaire Playability: High&amp;#10;Complexity Level: Medium&amp;#10;Players: 2 or more&amp;#10;Playing Time: 3-10 hours&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Note: Players will need to provide one 6-sided die for game play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
